dismissalText.commentary: Gordon Drummond c †Mohammad Shahzad b Shapoor Zadran 3 (4b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: oh my days! Drummond looks to go over the top to win the game and gets a thin edge through to the keeper. Afghanistan are delirious

commentTextItems.html: too full and Goudie angles the bat away, the ball races between cover and point and Goudie punches the air as he jogs the winning run

commentPostTextItems.html: Well, we should know by now that Scotland never make it easy again, but those 19 wides bowled by Afghanistan have cost them dear. A flurry of late wickets gave Afghanistan hope of a miracle but Goudie came in at number 10 to hit the winning runs.

Fraser Watts started the innings patiently and stuck about while the run rate lingered between 2-3 runs per over. There were two wickets a piece for Zadran, Nabi, Hassan and Mangal but eventual the Scots saw it home to claim a place in the final against Ireland tomorrow, who go unbeaten after beating the Netherlands by 39 runs.
The Scots are delighted and rightly so. They made hard work of it as usual and staggered over the line.
The man of the match has been awarded to Fraser Watts for his patient opening innings of 46 of 98 balls on a bowler-friendly track.
The Scots are now celebrating with a pint and singing O' Flower of Scotland at top volume in the dressing room, while for Afghanistan, their World Cricket League dream is over.

Thanks very much for joining us today for this match in Rotterdam between Scotland and Afghanistan where Scotland triumphed by the margin of two wickets. Do join us tomorrow for the play-off matches where the centrepiece will be the final between Scotland and Ireland at Amstelveen for the title of World Cricket League champions. (11.00am local, 9.00am GMT)
I will be there bringing you ball-by-ball commentary live from the ground, but for now it's Callum Stewart signing off from a sunny Rotterdam. Good afternoon.

commentTextItems.html: goes for the swipe on the off-side and carves the ball over point, third man's too fine and they run back for two. Scotland are in the final - scores are level

commentTextItems.html: drives hard at cover who fields on the bounce
cut away in front of point and they take two, almost there
angled away to gully

commentPostTextItems.html: Looks like Shapoor Zadran will come back on, much to the crowds delight, to try and keep the dream alive
Although Scotland need five to win, four runs will be enough to see them in to the final, as a tie would be enough because they are ahead of Afghanistan on nett run rate

commentTextItems.html: fuller ball dug away to midwicket
quick and full, beats Drummond but also the leg-stump and that's a wide. What Afghanistan would have done to not concede 19 wides in this game
short and with pace, Iqbal watches well and leaves
prods at the drive and a single down to third man

milestones.description: Hamid Hassan has become the top wicket-taker for AFG in ODIs with 15 wickets, going past Samiullah Shinwari's 14
This is the lowest match aggregate (283) involving teams Scotland & Afghanistan in ODIs
Asghar Afghan has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (10) for AFG, going past Mohammad Nabi

stories.title: Scotland make final after tight win
stories.subTitle: ICC World Cricket League Division One, 6th day
stories.seoTitle: ICC WCL Division 1: Scotland make final after tight win
stories.summary: Scotland experienced some hiccups in what was meant to be an easy chase, but held their nerve to beat Afghanistan by two wickets  and sealed their place in the World Cricket League Division One final with Ireland

image.caption: Gordon Goudie signals the win that took Scotland to the final
image.longCaption: Gordon Goudie signals the win that took Scotland to the final, Afghanistan v Scotland, ICC WCL Division 1, Rotterdam, July 9, 2010
